##What would you like to eat tomorrow

WECHAT denganqing1984

Features, here, I will share my writing, reading the book.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Every night around six o'clock, I would hear my mother downstairs shouting: "Qinger, I'm ready! " I immediately replied: "I know, I'LL BE RIGHT THERE! " Close the computer, put on shoes, wear a mask, take the mobile phone, and quickly ran downstairs. Mother's waiting at the top of the stairs.

Passing through the hall, my father, who was watching the news in the front room, turned and asked, "where are we going again? " I said, "to the supermarket. " My father said, "remember to buy me sugar-free milk. " My mother glared at him. "How quickly did you finish the last one I bought you? " My father recoiled, "My son bought it, you didn't buy it. It's up to you. " The mother continued, i pull her to walk, "Good Luo Good Luo, again want a few money! "

The light on the embankment was on. I took my mother's hand and went to the entrance of the embankment. The rape flowers on both sides of the road were in full bloom, and I sucked the fragrance of them voraciously. "every year can not see the rape flower, this year lets you see as much as possible! " The mother smiles.

She went on to say that there used to be a press at the edge of the rape field, and when the seeds were ready, they were sent there to be pressed. Rapeseed oil used to be a must for every family, and the stir-fried vegetables were delicious.

Because we grow cotton and peanuts here, so when we have cotton seeds and peanuts, we will also send them to the oil plant to be pressed for cottonseed oil and peanut oil. What they produced in those days, they put to use. It's not like we're going to the grocery store.
Actually, we didn't go to the supermarket much at first, after we shut down the city on January 24th. There are fresh vegetables in the garden, red vegetable sprouts, Shanghai Green, white radish have, now eat up, did not eat all the elders, can only go to the supermarket to buy wholesale vegetables.

There are three vegetable shops in our neighborhood. The nearest one used to be a barbershop. Now it also sells meat, eggs and vegetables, but there are not many varieties.

On the left-hand side, a supermarket 50 meters away from us was the first to open in the village. Before the closure of the city, every day was filled with people. Some people came to buy vegetables, and more people took this place as a center of activity, chatting, playing cards and basking in the Sun, after the outbreak, it was said that there had been a lull.

One hundred and fifty meters to the right is another supermarket, which is up and coming because it is so clean and clean compared to the one on the left. People who are used to big supermarkets in the city go to this one.
We chose the one on the right, not because it's clean, but because it's farthest. Shopping is secondary. Walking is the primary goal.

During the day everyone was shut up at home, and at night it was as if they were out of their cages, and along the way they saw small groups of women walking and talking, carrying things they had just bought from the supermarket.

My mother would have been with them, but she was all alone because she wanted to walk with me. When her mother met them, she stopped and said, "did you buy a baby? "

Talking to her aunt, open the bag, "pepper, eggplant, garlic... things are expensive oh! "

"Mother said:"that there is no way out? The House and no vegetables, do not buy line
I walked slowly in front, walking, his mother in the back shouted: "Qinger! Qinger! " I just found myself walking too fast, and back to meet her. I took her hand again, she said: "Do you want to eat tomorrow? " I said: "Go to the supermarket to see. "

The supermarket is always open in the evening and is not allowed to open during the day. As I expected, the supermarket is really crowded.

Everyone wearing masks, squatting on the ground to choose Tofu, tomatoes, cucumbers, etc. , frozen refrigerator, someone took out a packet of dumplings, a packet of quick-frozen dumplings, the checkout line up long... people are still too close to each other. Although we have no reports of anyone being infected.
Mother asked, "Do you want some? "

I said, "Do you want some? "

Mother patted my arm: "Don't be naughty. "

I seriously replied: "I really want to ask you. You always ask me, you have not thought of yourself. "

My mother smiled and said, "I have a son to think about. If you eat a son, I will eat with you. "

Talking and picking at the same time. At the checkout, $12 for three AUBERGINES, $twenty-four for a bag of flour, $60 for a carton of sugar free milk, and $4 for a few garlic cloves.

Mother tut-tut-tut-tut-tut-tut-tut-tut-tut-tut

I said, "it's not much money. It's fine. "

I was about to scan the Qr Code with my mobile phone when my mother stopped me and said, "you have to spend money again, ok? I have some change. "

I said: "You don't care thistle, this is not a piece of money. "

Mother, that's enough.
He went out with his hands full. Mother to take my things, I said: "You do not care, and not heavy. "

After a few steps, my mother insisted on taking some of the things in her hands. "It's strange how empty you are. "

I said: "usually I am in the room, was raised by you like a childe, now you when the Queen Mother also no problem. "

Mother still wouldn't listen, but she took the sack of flour.

"Mom, you spoil us all. In the end, you do all the work. You won't let us do it, because we'll get our clothes dirty and our hands wet, " I said

My mother looked at me. "I'm used to it. You do big things outside. You don't need to do small things. "
Although it was still under control, there were more cars on the national highway. We kept to the side of the road. There were no street lights on either side of the national highway, and the night was chiseled away by the headlights of the passing cars.

The wheels on the road issued rustle, the national road opposite to a group of people to the supermarket to buy things, they said with laughter.

When he reached the end of the dike, the car was gone and so was the man. His ears cleared away. My mother looked up and said, "look how many miles there are in the stars. " I looked up, too, and there, in the deep blue sky, was a grain of planetesimal.

Mother bowed her head and went on, "tomorrow seems to be a sunny day, you that bed quilt must be basked in. "
